messages.message: Python provisioner downloading pre-built image doesn't seem to work for fileservice. I think it's because the docker image is a different name from the provisioner service name. Anyone else have this issue?
Guessing this is the relevant PR: https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/42920/files cc @Heymian
ah just need to wrap the pull call in `_get_docker_service_name`. will create a PR
Hrm, I thought @Serena and @Cheryl Zhou fixed this right after ^ PR went in.
What’s the error you get lydia?
it can't find the scan image. probably because it's looking for file-service, but the image name is grpc-file-service
Oh this was the fix i was referring to https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/43377
yea i think it just missed the `ppy compile --as-docker --use-prebuilt` use case
Oh! That was the one case I didn’t test because prebuilt never worked for me :sweat_smile:
